The paper deals with drone navigation using visual input, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of convolutional neural networks for image processing and decision making suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the significance of data augmentation, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the application of the proposed approach in real-life scenarios involves system engineering and control (cs.SY).
